The paper proposes a vision-based navigation method for a multirotor vehicle, which involves solving a non-linear optimization problem and tracking the desired trajectory using a real-time Non-linear Model Predictive Controller (NMPC). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves using computer vision techniques such as Position-Based Visual Servoing (PBVS) and Image-Based Visual Servoing (IBVS), which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions meeting the UAV's dynamic constraints, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of optimization and control techniques also suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
